cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.CR 

The paper introduces a statistical relational learning system that uses neural networks to learn an implicit representation of first-order logic rules. This makes it relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), and cryptography (cs.CR). However, given the focus on learning and modelling distributions, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
